  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together dashi broth, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Place the lamb roast in a terracotta dish and brush the dashi mixture evenly over the lamb.",
    "Roast the lamb in the preheated oven for 20 minutes per pound, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 145 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Let the lamb rest for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy."
